UID:8031f3999fc3b89e2e18046ff90ab960d89846ae@macro-calendar.local
DTSTAMP:20260603T040514Z
DTSTART:20260617T180000Z
DTEND:20260617T190000Z
SUMMARY:🔥 US Fed: FOMC Interest Rate Decision
DESCRIPTION:Source: US Fed\nImpact: high\nOfficial Federal Reserve monthl
 y calendar FOMC meeting entry.\n\nExplainer:\n• What it is: Central Ba
 nk Rate Decision\n\n• Measures: Interest-rate decision\, policy statem
 ent and guidance from the central bank.\n\n• Usual market effect: More
  hawkish-than-expected guidance is usually bullish for the local currenc
 y and bearish for bonds. More dovish-than-expected guidance is usually b
 earish for the currency and bullish for bonds.\n\n• Why traders care: 
 Central-bank decisions directly affect interest rates\, currency valuati
 on\, bond yields and equity risk appetite.\n\n• Frequency: Scheduled s
 everal times per year.\n\n• Notes: The market often reacts not only to
  the rate decision\, but also to the statement\, forecasts\, press confe
 rence and tone.\n\n• Acronyms: FOMC = Federal Open Market Committee\; 
 RBA = Reserve Bank of Australia.\n\nOfficial source: https://www.federal
 reserve.gov/newsevents/2026-june.htm
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
BEGIN:VALARM
TRIGGER:-PT24H
ACTION:DISPLAY
DESCRIPTION:Tomorrow: 🔥 US Fed: FOMC Interest Rate Decision
END:VALARM
BEGIN:VALARM
TRIGGER:-PT30M
ACTION:DISPLAY
DESCRIPTION:30 minutes: 🔥 US Fed: FOMC Interest Rate Decision
END:VALARM
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:678644a10ad88089cf1fe5af4c195dba31c5a995@macro-calendar.local
DTSTAMP:20260603T040514Z
DTSTART:20260617T183000Z
DTEND:20260617T193000Z
SUMMARY:🔥 US Fed: FOMC Press Conference
DESCRIPTION:Source: US Fed\nImpact: high\nOfficial Federal Reserve monthl
 y calendar FOMC press conference entry.\n\nExplainer:\n• What it is: C
 entral Bank Rate Decision\n\n• Measures: Interest-rate decision\, poli
 cy statement and guidance from the central bank.\n\n• Usual market eff
 ect: More hawkish-than-expected guidance is usually bullish for the loca
 l currency and bearish for bonds. More dovish-than-expected guidance is 
 usually bearish for the currency and bullish for bonds.\n\n• Why trade
 rs care: Central-bank decisions directly affect interest rates\, currenc
 y valuation\, bond yields and equity risk appetite.\n\n• Frequency: Sc
 heduled several times per year.\n\n• Notes: The market often reacts no
 t only to the rate decision\, but also to the statement\, forecasts\, pr
 ess conference and tone.\n\n• Acronyms: FOMC = Federal Open Market Com
 mittee\; RBA = Reserve Bank of Australia.\n\nOfficial source: https://ww
 w.federalreserve.gov/newsevents/2026-june.htm
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
BEGIN:VALARM
TRIGGER:-PT24H
ACTION:DISPLAY
DESCRIPTION:Tomorrow: 🔥 US Fed: FOMC Press Conference
END:VALARM
