BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:07fcb1ea4a95f2efe45eac818262098cb7b1dfb2@macro-calendar.local
DTSTAMP:20260603T040514Z
DTSTART:20260624T013000Z
DTEND:20260624T020000Z
SUMMARY:🔥 AU ABS: Consumer Price Index\, Australia
DESCRIPTION:Source: AU ABS\nImpact: high\nReference period\n\nExplainer:\
 n• What it is: Consumer Price Index\n\n• Measures: Change in the pri
 ces paid by consumers for a basket of goods and services.\n\n• Usual m
 arket effect: Higher-than-forecast inflation is usually bullish for the 
 local currency and bearish for bonds\, because markets may price in high
 er interest rates.\n\n• Why traders care: CPI is one of the most watch
 ed inflation indicators because it can quickly shift central-bank rate e
 xpectations.\n\n• Frequency: US CPI is monthly. Australian CPI has bot
 h monthly indicator releases and quarterly CPI releases.\n\n• Notes: C
 ore CPI removes volatile items such as food and energy to give a cleaner
  read on underlying inflation pressure.\n\n• Acronyms: CPI = Consumer 
 Price Index.\n\nOfficial source: https://www.abs.gov.au/release-calendar
 /future-releases/202606/rcc_economy
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
BEGIN:VALARM
TRIGGER:-PT24H
ACTION:DISPLAY
DESCRIPTION:Tomorrow: 🔥 AU ABS: Consumer Price Index\, Australia
END:VALARM
BEGIN:VALARM
TRIGGER:-PT30M
ACTION:DISPLAY
DESCRIPTION:30 minutes: 🔥 AU ABS: Consumer Price Index\, Australia
END:VALARM
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:659594e646160d13bb908082b7c25c83078de9a6@macro-calendar.local
DTSTAMP:20260603T040514Z
DTSTART:20260624T013000Z
DTEND:20260624T020000Z
SUMMARY:🔥 AU ABS: Consumer Price Index\, Australia\, May 2026
DESCRIPTION:Source: AU ABS\nImpact: high\nOfficial ABS series page releas
 e date. Time zone shown by ABS: AEST.\n\nExplainer:\n• What it is: Con
 sumer Price Index\n\n• Measures: Change in the prices paid by consumer
 s for a basket of goods and services.\n\n• Usual market effect: Higher
 -than-forecast inflation is usually bullish for the local currency and b
 earish for bonds\, because markets may price in higher interest rates.\n
 \n• Why traders care: CPI is one of the most watched inflation indicat
 ors because it can quickly shift central-bank rate expectations.\n\n• 
 Frequency: US CPI is monthly. Australian CPI has both monthly indicator 
 releases and quarterly CPI releases.\n\n• Notes: Core CPI removes vola
 tile items such as food and energy to give a cleaner read on underlying 
 inflation pressure.\n\n• Acronyms: CPI = Consumer Price Index.\n\nOffi
 cial source: https://www.abs.gov.au/statistics/economy/price-indexes-and
 -inflation/consumer-price-index-australia
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
BEGIN:VALARM
