DESCRIPTION:Source: AU ABS\nImpact: high\nOfficial ABS series page releas
 e date. Time zone shown by ABS: AEST.\n\nExplainer:\n• What it is: Con
 sumer Price Index\n\n• Measures: Change in the prices paid by consumer
 s for a basket of goods and services.\n\n• Usual market effect: Higher
 -than-forecast inflation is usually bullish for the local currency and b
 earish for bonds\, because markets may price in higher interest rates.\n
 \n• Why traders care: CPI is one of the most watched inflation indicat
 ors because it can quickly shift central-bank rate expectations.\n\n• 
 Frequency: US CPI is monthly. Australian CPI has both monthly indicator 
 releases and quarterly CPI releases.\n\n• Notes: Core CPI removes vola
 tile items such as food and energy to give a cleaner read on underlying 
 inflation pressure.\n\n• Acronyms: CPI = Consumer Price Index.\n\nOffi
 cial source: https://www.abs.gov.au/statistics/economy/price-indexes-and
 -inflation/consumer-price-index-australia
