SUMMARY:🔥 AU ABS: Producer Price Indexes\, Australia\, June 2026
DESCRIPTION:Source: AU ABS\nImpact: high\nOfficial ABS series page releas
 e date. Time zone shown by ABS: AEST.\n\nExplainer:\n• What it is: Pro
 ducer Price Index\n\n• Measures: Change in prices received by producer
 s for goods and services.\n\n• Usual market effect: Higher-than-foreca
 st PPI can be bullish for the local currency if traders expect producer 
 inflation to flow through to consumer inflation.\n\n• Why traders care
 : PPI can provide an early signal of inflation pressure before it reache
 s consumers.\n\n• Frequency: Monthly in the US. Quarterly in Australia
 .\n\n• Notes: PPI is usually less market-moving than CPI\, but it can 
 still matter when inflation is the main macro theme.\n\n• Acronyms: PP
 I = Producer Price Index.\n\nOfficial source: https://www.abs.gov.au/sta
 tistics/economy/price-indexes-and-inflation/producer-price-indexes-austr
 alia
