 n• What it is: Producer Price Index\n\n• Measures: Change in prices 
 received by producers for goods and services.\n\n• Usual market effect
 : Higher-than-forecast PPI can be bullish for the local currency if trad
 ers expect producer inflation to flow through to consumer inflation.\n\n
 • Why traders care: PPI can provide an early signal of inflation press
 ure before it reaches consumers.\n\n• Frequency: Monthly in the US. Qu
 arterly in Australia.\n\n• Notes: PPI is usually less market-moving th
 an CPI\, but it can still matter when inflation is the main macro theme.
 \n\n• Acronyms: PPI = Producer Price Index.\n\nOfficial source: https:
 //www.abs.gov.au/release-calendar/future-releases/202607
