SUMMARY:🔥 AU ABS: Average Weekly Earnings\, Australia
DESCRIPTION:Source: AU ABS\nImpact: high\nReference period\n\nExplainer:\
 n• What it is: Wage Price Index / Average Earnings\n\n• Measures: Ch
 ange in wages and earnings.\n\n• Usual market effect: Higher-than-fore
 cast wage growth can be bullish for the local currency if traders expect
  stronger inflation pressure and tighter central-bank policy.\n\n• Why
  traders care: Wage growth can feed into inflation and is closely watche
 d by central banks.\n\n• Frequency: Monthly or quarterly depending on 
 release.\n\n• Notes: Strong wages can be positive for consumers but ca
 n also increase inflation pressure.\n\n• Acronyms: WPI = Wage Price In
 dex.\n\nOfficial source: https://www.abs.gov.au/release-calendar/future-
 releases/202608
