SUMMARY:🔥 US Fed: FOMC Interest Rate Decision
DESCRIPTION:Source: US Fed\nImpact: high\nOfficial Federal Reserve monthl
 y calendar FOMC meeting entry.\n\nExplainer:\n• What it is: Central Ba
 nk Rate Decision\n\n• Measures: Interest-rate decision\, policy statem
 ent and guidance from the central bank.\n\n• Usual market effect: More
  hawkish-than-expected guidance is usually bullish for the local currenc
 y and bearish for bonds. More dovish-than-expected guidance is usually b
 earish for the currency and bullish for bonds.\n\n• Why traders care: 
 Central-bank decisions directly affect interest rates\, currency valuati
 on\, bond yields and equity risk appetite.\n\n• Frequency: Scheduled s
 everal times per year.\n\n• Notes: The market often reacts not only to
  the rate decision\, but also to the statement\, forecasts\, press confe
 rence and tone.\n\n• Acronyms: FOMC = Federal Open Market Committee\; 
 RBA = Reserve Bank of Australia.\n\nOfficial source: https://www.federal
 reserve.gov/newsevents/2026-october.htm
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
